  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to Rohingya Refugees and Host Communities Through Shelter and COVID-19 Health Interventions, Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under this project, IOM provides support to Rohingya refugees and host communities in Bangladesh through shelter and COVID-19 health specific interventions. IOM is providing support to Rohingya refugees through the Transitional Shelter Assistance 2 (TSA2) which aims to improve and maintain the existing shelters with shelter trainings and distribution of durable shelter materials in the IOM Area of Responsibility camps. As a pilot, IOM is also constructing 2-storey steel frame shelters which was newly designed to provide durable shelter and ease the density across camps in Kutupalong Balukhali and Expansions and Teknaf areas. IOM is involved in the key thematic areas in the COVID-19 response including case management and referrals; interventions in risk communication and community engagement; surveillance and contact tracing; support to testing through sample collection; infection prevention and control; capacity building; operations and logistics as well as lead roles in coordination and partnerships.</narrative>
  </description>
